1614, "(fr)Capital ship stand off.  Multiplayer mission.  Max respawns 10.  Recommended respawns 5."

1615, "(fr)Terran intelligence has received the coordinates of the Apophis, a Hammer of Light Typhon-class destroyer.  Your mission: ambush and obliterate this vessel."

1616, "(fr)The commander of the Apophis is Admiral Kek, the highest-ranking officer to defect since the formation of the Terran-Vasudan alliance and the HOL insurgency."

1617, "(fr)Deep-cover Vasudan operatives within Hammer of Light have advised intelligence of the destroyer's location.  Because we are the alliance force in closest proximity to these coordinates, command has ordered the GTD Hephaestus to launch an immediate attack."

1618, "(fr)The Epona has also been deployed to assist and will reinforce our assault once the cruiser is in position."

1619, "(fr)Expect to encounter heavy resistance.  Admiral Kek inspires absolute loyalty in his followers.  We must be willing to make any sacrifice necessary to destroy the Apophis."

1620, "(fr)Excellent work, pilot.  You destroyed the Apophis, and the GTD Hephaestus sustained only minor damage.  Command anticipates the death of Admiral Kek will undermine the morale and strategic leadership of Hammer of Light."

1621, "(fr)You eliminated Admiral Kek and his capital ship.  However, the GTD Hephaestus sustained Dégâts Élevés.  Extensive repairs will be required before we bring the ship back on line.  This may compromise allied operations in this sector."

1622, "(fr)Use some wingmen to defend the Hephaestus."

1623, "(fr)Command deeply regrets the loss of the GTD Hephaestus and its crew.  However, our task force accomplished its objective.  With the death of Admiral Kek and the destruction of the Apophis, the alliance has achieved a significant victory over Hammer of Light."

1624, "(fr)Command has ordered court-martial proceedings, pilot.  What should have been a triumph for the alliance resulted in humiliating defeat.  Admiral Kek and the Apophis destroyed the GTD Hephaestus and escaped."

